Subject: [PATCH 3/4] Use Wide formatting style for separating type parameter
 constraints

While the "Compressed" punctuation style is suitable for most occasions, the
formatting of generic parameter constraints looks off without spaces.
Unfortunately, however, it cannot be configured on its own.
So with this change we force the "Wide" style to be used for those
cases.
---
 src/tools/rustfmt/src/types.rs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/tools/rustfmt/src/types.rs b/src/tools/rustfmt/src/types.rs
index 7b23cd..9e97e4 100644
--- a/src/tools/rustfmt/src/types.rs
+++ b/src/tools/rustfmt/src/types.rs
@@ -756,7 +756,7 @@ fn join_bounds(
 
     // Try to join types in a single line
     let joiner = match context.config.type_punctuation_density() {
-        TypeDensity::Compressed => "+",
+        TypeDensity::Compressed |
         TypeDensity::Wide => " + ",
     };
     let type_strs = items
